=Description=

"Our November 2006 Internet Advocacy Roundtable featured a discussion on MySpace Campaign Case Studies with speakers, Scott Goodstein (Catalyst Campaigns), Ivan Boothe (Genocide Intervention Network), and Jeff Goldsmith (DeadElephant.org), who have run real campaigns on MySpace and other online social networks. They discussed the practical issues they faced in their efforts to tap the huge potential of online social network communities for advocacy campaigns.
	 
* Scott Goodstein, President, Catalyst Campaigns
    
* Ivan Boothe, Director of Communications, Genocide Intervention Network
    
* Jeff Goldsmith, Founder, DeadElephant.org
    

